<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12119c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12119c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12119c"> 119(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cock crows at night</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le meilleur avertisseur de la basse-cour est inconstablement le coq. S&apos;il crie comme un perdu, s&apos;<mark>il lance son cocorico &agrave;une heure insolite de la nuit</i>, mauvais pr&eacute;sage. <small> Fran&ccedil;ois Cadic, <a name="NCEL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#NCEL"><cite title="source">Nouveaux contes et l&eacute;gendes de Bretagne</cite></a> (1922) 44</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: According to Breton legend, if the cock crows in the night before midnight, it signifies great misfortune, an accident, or death.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c12122g" href="c12all.htm#c12122g">VI.C.12:122(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
